  "text": "Rockafellar and Uryasev [CITATION_1] showed that the set of optimal solutions to this stochastic program is given by S := [c, c], where c = sup{t : F (t) ≤ p}. Note that c ∈ S, it then follows Equation (1). To estimate the CVaR of X, Trindade et al. [CITATION_2] suggested to use the sample average approximation of (15)",
